You form relationships in life by being vulnerable.

I believe it‚Äôs why so many people come up to me recognizing me at conferences or at random places to share their stories about their health.

What they had to overcome.

I will be vulnerable now.

The sheer outpouring of messages on my DMs - I am blown away.

Been tearing up literally in a coffee shop reading. 

I had a moment of significant weakness yesterday that sent me into a dark place.

I‚Äôm tired of running in this dark place.

I‚Äôm tired of feeling abandoned by those I was there for whom I thought would be there for the journey.

I said a few days ago I did it alone before, and I‚Äôll do it alone again.

And while that is true, I see I am not alone.

We are not alone.

The truth is the worst feeling in the world is feeling like you‚Äôre running in place.

It goes beyond my funds.

It goes beyond my content.

It goes beyond a persona.

It goes to the heart of what struggle is. 

A lack of hope that the environment will change, daily toiling away and running.

All while those you work with are thriving, enjoying life, building, succeeding.

I said before it can turn you bitter.

It did.

I am in truth very tried. I lost something extremely important the last 6 weeks - my confidence. 

I see so many people thriving and succeeding while I‚Äôm working hard every day to enrich others, hoping for my punch in life (my funds) to burn bright like a phoenix.

I felt this before in 2019 before the biggest year of my life financially when I had the success I so yearned for.

It got ripped away from me, and I got kicked to the floor.

But I‚Äôm still here, and to those who have sent such incredible and beautiful messages to me? Thank you for being vulnerable. For not lending your hand to me. Rather, for opening your heart on the very floor I fell on.

I will rise. 

I have no choice.

We have no choice.
I‚Äôm right about deregulation and free markets.
